Title: From Bottom of the Barrel to Cream of the Crop: Sequential Screening With Positive Selection 
Author-Name: Jean Tirole  
Abstract:
  In a number of interesting environments, dynamic screening involves
 positive selection: in contrast with Coasian dynamics, only the most
 motivated remain over time. The paper provides conditions under which the
 principal's commitment optimum is time consistent and uses this result to
 derive testable predictions under permanent or transient shocks. It also
 identifies environments in which time consistency does not hold despite
 positive selection, and yet simple equilibrium characterizations can be
 obtained. 
